desc_long									最新更新									Service Pack 1 for Tower 3D is now live and will be an automatic update for all users of the Steam edition. Any future purchasers of Tower 3D from Steam will also automatically receive Service Pack 1. Changes included in Service Pack 1:Darker radar backgroundsReset statistic button added Smaller airplane icon on the radar screenSeparated the sound slider for environment and airplane soundsSelectable pilot voices. Note: you can choose between male or female, speed and tone or make it random (Male voice needs to be installed for some of the settings to work, and is not included with Windows 7) Gates connect to the front door Added airport traffic density slider Beacon lights will be turned off only at the gate Departing airplanes now line up quicker for takeoff All airplanes should now hold short of each runway Smaller glow for the airport lights Better logic for the runway alert warnings Added adjustable heading slider for arriving airplanes Fixed KPHL runway 8/26 no escape error Fixed toobright taxi and runway lights at night Fixed bug with collision between parking and taxiing planes on KLAX at TBIT Fixed bug in which loading won't advance beyond 70% for some users Fixed bug where START button is inactive for some users																						关于这款游戏							Your assignment is to guide aircraft of various sizes and capabilities to and from the active runway for landing and takeoff. To help you to assure the safe movement of the airplanes on the ground and in the air Tower!3D provides flight strips, ground and air radar screens and full 3D views of the airport.3 photorealistic airportsAdvanced AI pilots to follow your commandsStunning 3D rendering of the airportsRunway assignments for arriving and departing aircraft may be changedRunway intersection takeoffs are simulatedAdvanced routing to and from the runways and terminals can be assignedDynamic lighting and shadows, day-night cycles provide a stunning visual experienceLive airport with service cars for airplanes and vehicle traffic around the airports						
